    "similar_bugs_context": {
      "common_patterns": [
        "Crashes related to memory allocation failures during garbage collection",
        "OOM (Out Of Memory) crashes occurring in the JS engine nursery",
        "Failures specifically triggered while trying to allocate new memory chunks for GC"
      ],
      "potential_root_causes": [
        "Insufficient memory available for the JavaScript engine's nursery during GC",
        "Potential memory leaks or excessive memory usage in the code paths related to RTX Video Super Resolution feature",
        "Inefficient or incorrect handling of memory allocation requests leading to GC failures"
      ],
      "relevant_fix_clues": [
        "The meta bug description highlights 'Failed to allocate new chunk during GC', indicating the crash is caused by running out of memory in the nursery space",
        "No explicit status or resolution is provided in the similar bugs, suggesting they might still be open or unresolved",
        "If resolved, typical fixes would involve optimizing memory usage or increasing nursery size to prevent allocation failures"
      ],
      "summary": "These similar bugs suggest that the crashes share a common pattern of out-of-memory failures within the JavaScript engine's garbage collection process, specifically during nursery chunk allocations. This points to a root cause related to insufficient or fragmented memory when enabling features like NVIDIA RTX Video Super Resolution. Addressing this likely requires memory usage optimizations or adjustments to GC memory management."
    }
  },
